{"id":1734941,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-21T12:47:06.276Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":878,"name":"Science Fiction"}],"homepage":"","id":1734941,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["CA"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Nominal","overview":"2046. Corporations are using repressed memories to secure sensitive data against hacking.  K lives in isolation inside a sterile memory compound, subjected to daily interrogations designed to excavate and erase a single buried memory. As fragments resurface through recurring dreams of fire, panic, and a lost child, he struggles to separate genuine recollection from manufactured reconstruction.  Guided deeper by a calm, invasive corporate system, K is forced to confront a tragedy tied to his sister and the guilt he has carried ever since. But as the sessions intensify, a darker truth emerges: his trauma is not being treated. It is being weaponised. His unresolved grief is a living encryption key, and the corporation is using his subconscious to breach a protected mental firewall.  Nominal is a psychological sci-fi noir about memory, grief, and the commodification of consciousness, in a world where even trauma is bought and sold.","popularity":0.0143,"poster_path":"/aFKBxQ1joHXZ6UHcB1hTZbecj5o.jpg","production_companies":[],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"CA","name":"Canada"}],"release_date":"2026-07-25","revenue":0,"runtime":8,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"English","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English"}],"status":"In Production","tagline":"","title":"Nominal","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":5532369,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Lucas Duncan","original_name":"Lucas Duncan","popularity":0,"profile_path":null,"cast_id":1,"character":"","credit_id":"6a5e900b8589da0ab502065e","order":0},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":6360401,